<br>
he said;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get DS just 1-2pt less than mage and greater with ancient.&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   <br>
Druid DS spell at 58 is Shield of Blades 32dmg single target, 59 is Legacy of Thorn 28dmg group and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Ancient: </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Legacy of Blade is 36dmg group.  Does anyone have the last spell listed yet?   Mages have at lvl 60 Aegis of Ro 33dmg+33FR group.  Druids get better, but only with there Ancient spell.  thanks. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get pets (better than SK'z which is a staple of their class)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   <br>
You are kidding me right?  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get HUGH DD (sorry wizz)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Wizzy's nuke better by far, especially now with manaburn.  Have you not read all that has been posted in this thread so far?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get heals (sorry clerics-- who else is gonna heal ya aside from a sham.. a BST?)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->   <br>
Yes we get heals, but for raiding we can have a very hard time.  Usually healing lighter melee and casters.  And shammy's can heal a rodding cleric just fine with Torpor once they get slow's off. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-mana regen -- potg (sorry chanter)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Familiars?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get buffz - lots and lots of buffs&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
On raids I PotG, seasons if needed and heal.  I'm not 59, but before PotC came out Glades was hardly used with Aego being tossed around. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get dots (sorry necs)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
We dont come close to doing better than Necro's on DoT's.  Druid best DoT is WD at 53 with 1287dmg over 54secs with 350mana Magic based.  Hell I think shammy's get better DoT's then Druids do?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they can quad (much more efficiently than anyone)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Thank god there's something we can do good, but just totally pisses everyone off cuz it's used to get exp sometimes.  Wish I could get into more AE groups...that makes Quading exp look like poop.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get ports (Poor duids, can't port right to the moon)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Yea no moon port sux.....but &lt;3 Binding.   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;-they get sow (yay we all love sow)&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <br>
Rangers, Shammy's, Beasty's?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Not flaming what he said.  I just think this guy proves that Druids might be a &quot;Jack of All Trades&quot; but in the &quot;end-game&quot; who gives a crap.  I love playing my Druid on higher end stuff and I have a blast.  The way they have taken the game just makes me feel like I spent 58 levels for nothing now cuz I like to do the higher lvl stuff (raiding), but play a character that doesn't have one solid contribution like others do.  I think we should start a post about a new area all together that Druids could be the master of, without stepping on anyone's toes at all.  <br>
<br>
As far as Nuking, I don't care.  There are plenty of nuker's in the game.  A section of the game that could use some more people, I think, is healing.  I heal more than anything on raids as it is.  What sux is when I have to dump a ton of mana on a melee who lost a couple bubbles of health from getting caught by a rampage.  <br>
<br>
I think it would be really cool if we could be put in the #1 slot of a whole new aspect that could be added to the game.  Thing is, like with any change the impliment, they have to make sure not to totally upset the whole balance of the game altogether.  We are the master of animals, but c'mon, how much does that actually benefit others....especially on higher level raids.  <br>
